  "prompt": "Are there specific laws targeting money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, many countries have specific laws targeting money laundering. In the United States, the primary anti-money laundering (AML) laws include the Bank Secrecy Act and the USA PATRIOT Act. These laws require financial institutions to:\n\n1. Implement customer identification programs\n2. Report suspicious transactions\n3. Maintain records of financial transactions\n4. Comply with monitoring and reporting requirements\n\nInternationally, organizations like the Financial Action Task Force (FATF) set global standards for combating money laundering. Penalties for money laundering can include significant fines and criminal prosecution.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of money laundering laws?",
